      • add

        public void add(java.lang.String key,
                java.lang.Object value)
         throws JsonElementNotFoundException
        This method is for adding/updating property into root JsonObject
        Parameters:
        key - key is at level 1 If JsonObject is found by key, JsonObject will replace its value by new value If JsonObject is NOT found by key, JsonObject will be created with value
        value - value could be Number, String, Boolean, Character
        Throws:
        JsonElementNotFoundException

      • addMap

        public void addMap(java.lang.String parentKey,
                   java.lang.String key,
                   java.lang.Object value)
            throws JsonElementNotFoundException
        This method is for adding/updating JsonObject with parentKey into root JsonObject

        If JsonObject (child) is found by parentKey - JsonObject (child) will add property with key and value - Then JsonObject (child) will be added into root JsonObject If JsonObject (child) is NOT found by parentKey - JsonObject (child) will be created - JsonObject (child) will add property with key and value - Then JsonObject (child) will be added into root JsonObject

        Parameters:
        parentKey - parentKey is at level 1
        key -
        value -
        Throws:
        JsonElementNotFoundException

      • addArrayValue

        public void addArrayValue(java.lang.String key,
                          java.lang.Object value)
                   throws JsonElementNotFoundException
        This method is for adding/updating a JsonArray of values into root JsonObject

        If JsonArray (child) is found by key: - JsonArray (child) will add value as a JsonPrimitive - JsonArray (child) will be added into root JsonObject If JsonArray (child) is NOT found by key - JsonArray (child) will be created and then add value - JsonArray (child) will be added into root JsonObject

        Parameters:
        key - key is at level 1
        value -
        Throws:
        JsonElementNotFoundException

      • addArrayMap

        public void addArrayMap(java.lang.String parentKey,
                        java.lang.String key,
                        java.lang.Object value)
                 throws JsonElementNotFoundException
        This method is for adding/updating a map (key - value) in an array with parentKey

        If JsonArray (child) is found by parentKey - If index is given, JsonArray will looking for JsonObject with that index + if JsonObject is found, it will be added property (key - value) + if JsonObject is NOT found, new JsonObject will be create and and property (key-value) - If index is NOT given, new JsonObject will be added into first If JsonArray (child) is NOT found by parentKey - JsonArray will be created and add JsonObject (key - value)

        Parameters:
        parentKey - parentKey is at level 1 parentKey could be: - single value. Example: Name - single value and index. Example: Name[2]
        key -
        value -
        Throws:
        JsonElementNotFoundException - Example: Command: body.addArrayMap("Name", "Firstname", "Jason"); Output: { "Name": [ { "Firstname": "Jason" } ] }

        Command: body.addArrayMap("Name[0]", "Lastname", "Kai"); or body.addArrayMap("Name", "Lastname", "Kai"); Output: { "Name": [ { "Firstname": "Jason", "Lastname": "Kai" } ] }

        Command: body.addArrayMap("Name[1]", "FirstName", "Kai");] Output: { "Name": [ { "Firstname": "Jason", "Lastname": "Kai" }, { "FirstName": "Kai" } ] }
